.TH "check_dev_quirk" 9 "check_dev_quirk" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
check_dev_quirk \- apply early quirks to a given PCI device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" check_dev_quirk
.BI "(int num "  ","
.BI "int slot "  ","
.BI "int func "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "num" 12
bus number
.IP "slot" 12
slot number
.IP "func" 12
PCI function
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Check the vendor & device ID against the early quirks table.

If the device is single function, let \fBearly_pci_scan_bus\fP know so we don't
poke at this device again.
